               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Sharḥ al-Māhīyah al-aḥmadīyah va al-ḥaqīqah al-muḥammadīyah by Abu al-Maḥāsin Muḥammad Ṣadr al-ʻĀlam</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/sh2008112365" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1070-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>On the Sufi theosophical doctrine of the concept of Muḥammad as the perfect man and the world orders revolving round him, by Abu al-Maḥāsin Muḥammad Ṣadr al-ʻĀlam.</p>
                        <p>Contains two diagrams (f.2r and 110r).</p>
                        <p>ff 110; 17 lines to a page; shikastah; very worm-eaten; 18th century.</p>
                     </note>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f8038">Abu al-Maḥāsin Muḥammad Ṣadr al-ʻĀlam</persName>
